Description: Shoulder sherd of East Greek pottery closed vessel, amphora or large oinochoe; exterior: cream slip (partly worn); inscription on exterior.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis), Stratum AP20
Curator's comments: The number in Petrie's catalogue, 326, is written in ink on the exterior surface of the sherd. AP20 (more likely than 'AP10') is written in pencil on the interior surface of the sherd.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 326)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 670, no. 287)
Möller 2000 / Naukratis, Trade in Archaic Greece (180)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.950)
